Question:
Partition strings by whether they contain the letter 'a'.

Input:
List<String> vals = Arrays.asList("table", "chair", "desk", "sofa");

Solutions:-

Java 8 Streams partition strings by 'a' presence using Collectors.partitioningBy(s -> s.contains("a")). For input ["table", "chair", "desk", "sofa"], true=["table"], false=["chair", "desk", "sofa"].

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream strings → collect(partitioningBy(contains "a")) → Map<Boolean, List<String>>.

#Complete Implementation

import java.util.*;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;

public class PartitionByA {
    public static Map<Boolean, List<String>> partitionByA(List<String> vals) {
        return vals.stream()
                   .collect(Collectors.partitioningBy(s -> s.contains("a")));
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<String> vals = Arrays.asList("table", "chair", "desk", "sofa");
        Map<Boolean, List<String>> partitioned = partitionByA(vals);
        
        System.out.println("Contains 'a': " + partitioned.get(true));
        System.out.println("No 'a': " + partitioned.get(false));
    }
}

Output:

text
Contains 'a': [table]
No 'a': [chair, desk, sofa]

#Thought Process
partitioningBy creates boolean-keyed Map (true/false). String.contains("a") case-sensitive predicate. Single-pass O(n). Access results via get(true)/get(false). Preserves encounter order within partitions.

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: {true=[], false=[]}
All contain 'a': {true=[all], false=[]}
No 'a': {true=[], false=[all]}
Empty strings: "".contains("a") = false
Null list: NPE on stream()
Null elements: null.contains("a") NPE
